1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,860
My partner tells me that your crew switched
to a P2P cook because of our success.

2
00:00:09,380 --> 00:00:12,920
You dye your meth with food
coloring to make it look like mine.

3
00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:16,280
You already ape my product at every turn.

4
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:21,580
But now, you have the
opportunity to sell it yourself.

5
00:00:22,320 --> 00:00:23,420
I need you to listen to me.

6
00:00:23,920 --> 00:00:27,620
We're not going to give up this deal to be
your errand boys, do you understand me?

7
00:00:29,621 --> 00:00:30,820
For what?

8
00:00:31,060 --> 00:00:33,180
To watch a bunch of
junkies get a better high?

9
00:00:33,380 --> 00:00:36,920
A better high means customers pay more.

10
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:41,260
A higher purity means a greater yield.

11
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:49,040
That's $130 million of profit that isn't
being pissed away by some substandard cook.

12
00:00:49,820 --> 00:00:50,940
Now, you listen to me.

13
00:00:53,141 --> 00:00:55,040
You've got the greatest
meth cook in America.

14
00:00:55,120 --> 00:00:59,500
No, the two greatest meth
cooks in America right here.

15
00:00:59,780 --> 00:01:06,240
And with our skills, you'll earn more from
that 35% than you ever would on your own.

16
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:07,040
Yeah.

17
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:08,720
That's what you say.

18
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:10,340
Just wondering why we're so lucky.

19
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:12,440
Why cut us in?

20
00:01:13,041 --> 00:01:16,829
Mike is retiring from our
crew, so his share of the

21
00:01:16,841 --> 00:01:21,240
partnership is available
if you can handle his end.

22
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:23,240
Distribution.

23
00:01:24,100 --> 00:01:27,681
And if you give him $5 million of
the $15 million that you brought

24
00:01:27,693 --> 00:01:31,340
today, just think of it as a
finder's fee for bringing us together.

25
00:01:32,940 --> 00:01:35,720
We have 40 pounds of product ready to ship.

26
00:01:36,220 --> 00:01:37,220
Ready to go.

27
00:01:39,140 --> 00:01:40,100
Are you ready?

28
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:03,320
Who the hell are you?

29
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:04,920
You know.

30
00:02:05,120 --> 00:02:07,760
You all know exactly who I am.

31
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:12,300
Say my name.

32
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:14,440
Do what?

33
00:02:14,980 --> 00:02:17,320
I don't have a damn
clue who the hell you are.

34
00:02:17,340 --> 00:02:18,340
Yeah, you do.

35
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:19,680
I'm the cook.

36
00:02:22,340 --> 00:02:24,760
I'm the man who killed Gus Fring.

37
00:02:25,460 --> 00:02:26,460
Bullshit.

38
00:02:26,660 --> 00:02:27,660
Cartel got Fring.

39
00:02:28,620 --> 00:02:29,120
You sure?

40
00:02:40,321 --> 00:02:40,940
That's right.

41
00:02:41,841 --> 00:02:46,000
Now, say my name.

42
00:02:51,580 --> 00:02:52,260
Heisenberg.

43
00:02:54,941 --> 00:02:56,641
You're goddamn right.

